d administrative resources into law enforcement and border securitization at the expense of social services has led to the convergence of illicit smuggling and organ trading networks and the development of organized crime. Trading Life delivers a powerful and grounded analysis of how economic pressures and the demands of survival force people into exploitative arrangements, like selling a kidney, that they would otherwise avoid. This fascinating and accessible book is a must-read for anyone interested in migration, organized crime, and exploitation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aDonation of organs, tissues, etcxEconomic aspectszEgyptzCairo. 0aDonation of organs, tissues, etc.xEconomic aspectszEgyptzCairo. 0aIllegal alienszEgyptzCairoxEconomic conditions. 0aOrgan traffickingzEgyptzCairo. 0aSale of organs, tissues, etczEgyptzCairo. 0aSale of organs, tissues, etc.zEgyptzCairo. 0aTransplantation of organs, tissues, etc.xSocial aspectszEgyptzCairo. 7aLAW / Criminal Law / General.2bisacsh  aOrgan trafficking.  aexploitation.  aillegal markets.  aillegal migration.  aillicit networks.  aorgan trade.  aorgan transplantation.  aorganized crime.  apeople smuggling.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020 Englishz978311070486008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Law 2020z9783110704587oZDB-23-DGC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069218140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361256340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503612563423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/c